This paper involves the use of vision-based navigation and language-based assistance, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also utilizes computer vision techniques to perceive the environment (cs.CV) and robotics techniques for navigation (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for imitation learning (cs.LG) to model language-based assistance.
